article.description: — Tristen Newton had 27 points as East Carolina narrowly beat Tulsa 64-59 on Saturday.
article.headline: Newton scores 27 to carry East Carolina over Tulsa 64-59
article.linkText: Newton scores 27 to carry East Carolina over Tulsa 64-59
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. -- — Tristen Newton had 27 points as East Carolina narrowly beat Tulsa 64-59 on Saturday. Players were ejected after flagrant fouls following the clinching free throws by Alexis Reyes at the end of the game. Vance Jackson had 12 points for East Carolina (15-13, 6-10 American Athletic Conference). Ludgy Debaut added three assists. The Pirates forced a season-high 20 turnovers. Darien Jackson had 17 points for the Golden Hurricane (9-18, 3-13). Jeriah Horne added 14 points. Curtis Haywood II had six rebounds. The Pirates improve to 2-0 against the Golden Hurricane this season. East Carolina defeated Tulsa 73-71 on Feb. 8. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
